Skytable database server daemon (skyd): database file optimization utility

Details:
  The `compact` subcommand optimizes the database files by removing any stale or deleted
  data and/or applying other operations. This can help improve database performance,
  efficiency and reduce disk usage.

Usage: skyd compact

Informational flags:
  -h, --help                    Display this help menu and exit.
  -v, --version                 Display the version number and exit.

Examples:
  skyd compact

Notes:
    - This command will force a compaction even if it is not required
    - All data is backed up prior to compaction in the 'backups/' directory in a folder
    named using the following template 'YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS-before-compaction'

{further_assistance}